'''"Ooh, What a Life"''' ("Ooh" on label, "Oooh" on sleeve, often "Oh" in print sources) is a 1979 song by the [[Gibson Brothers]]. It was a UK No.10 hit. [[Joey Negro]]'s 1993 debut album included a version of the song.<ref>Colin Larkin, Muze UK Ltd ''The Virgin encyclopedia of nineties music'' 2000- Page 209 "Joey Negro's 1993 debut included a version of the Gibson Brothers' 'Oooh What A Life', featuring Gwen Guthrie. "</ref>

